  "prompt": "What are the properties of orthoboric acid?",
  "response": "Orthoboric acid (H3BO3), also known as boric acid, has several important properties:\n\nPhysical Properties:\n1. Appearance: White, crystalline solid\n2. Melting point: 170\u00b0C (338\u00b0F)\n3. Boiling point: 300\u00b0C (572\u00b0F)\n4. Solubility: Soluble in water, slightly soluble in alcohol\n5. Density: 1.435 g/cm\u00b3\n\nChemical Properties:\n1. Weak acid (pKa \u2248 9.2)\n2. Non-toxic in low concentrations\n3. Acts as a Lewis acid\n4. Forms borates when reacted with metals\n5. Can act as a mild antiseptic and preservative\n\nStructural Properties:\n1. Planar molecular structure\n2. Hydrogen bonding between molecules\n3. Trigonal geometry around boron atom\n\nPractical Applications:\n1. Antiseptic and medical uses\n2. Insecticide and pesticide\n3. Glass and ceramic manufacturing\n4. Flame retardant\n5. Preservative in cosmetics and pharmaceuticals\n\nThese properties make orthoboric acid versatile and useful in various industries and applications.",
